<HL>
   Intital State Jobless Claims
   Fell in Week Ended Dec. 8
</HL>
<DATE>
12/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
U.S. ECONOMIC INDICATORS (EMI)
FORECASTS AND ANALYSIS OF U.S. ECONOMIC INDICATORS (EMJ)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Initial claims for state unemployment
insurance fell to a seasonally adjusted 455,000 in the week
ended Dec. 8 from 471,000 in the previous week, the Labor
Department said.
   In the week ended Dec. 1, the number of people receiving
regular state unemployment benefits totaled 2,953,000, or
2.8% of those covered by unemployment insurance, down from
3,004,000 in the previous week, when the insured unemployment
rate was 2.9%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Counting all state and federal benefit programs, the
number of people receiving unemployment benefits in the week
ended Dec. 1 fell to 2,989,000 from 3,094,000 in the previous
week. These figures aren't seasonally adjusted.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
