<HL>
   Commodity Funds Gain
</HL>
<DATE>
12/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<IN>
MUTUAL AND MONEY-MARKET FUNDS (FND)
COMMODITY NEWS, FARM PRODUCTS (CMD)
</IN>
<LP>
   CHICAGO -- The average gain of 134 publicly offered
commodity funds was 0.3% in November, according to Norwood
Securities, which tracks fund performance.
   Norwood said that followed an average gain of 0.7% for
October, and brought the average gain for the first 11 months
of the year to 20.4%.
</LP>
