<HL>
   Sunshine Mining Unit's Venture
</HL>
<DATE>
12/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   SSC MLRC
</CO>
<IN>
DIVERSIFIED MINING (MNG)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Sunshine Mining Co. said a subsidiary formed a
joint venture with a subsidiary of Mallon Resources Corp. and
Red Rock Ventures Inc., to explore for gold in the Guanacaste
Province of Costa Rica.
   Pending the analysis of results from a 36-hole drilling
program, Sunshine Mining has the option to acquire a 50%
interest in and become manager of the venture. If Sunshine
chooses to proceed, Mallon will retain a 35% interest in the
project and Red Rock Ventures will retain a 15% stake.
</LP>
