</IN>
<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
FEDERAL RESERVE BOARD (FED)
</GV>
<LP>
   Thursday, December 20, 1990
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   The key U.S. and foreign annual interest rates below are a
guide to general levels but don't always represent actual
transactions.
                                                                                                       

   PRIME RATE: 9 1/2%-10%. The base rate on corporate loans
at large U.S. money center commercial banks.
                                                                                                       

   FEDERAL FUNDS: 7 3/16% high, 7 1/16% low, 7 3/16% near
closing bid, 7 3/16% offered. Reserves traded among
commercial banks for overnight use in amounts of $1 million
or more. Source: Babcock Fulton Prebon (U.S.A.) Inc.
                                                                                                       

   DISCOUNT RATE: 6.50%. The charge on loans to depository
institutions by the New York Federal Reserve Bank.
                                                                                                       

   CALL MONEY: 9% to 9 1/2%. The charge on loans to brokers
on stock exchange collateral.
                                                                                                       

   COMMERCIAL PAPER placed directly by General Motors
Acceptance Corp.: 7.55% 30 to 44 days; 7.15% 45 to 59 days;
7.10% 60 to 89 days; 7.05% 90 to 119 days; 7% 120 to 149
days; 6.85% 150 to 270 days.
                                                                                                       

   COMMERCIAL PAPER: High-grade unsecured notes sold through
dealers by major corporations in multiples of $1,000: 8.10%
30 days; 7.85% 60 days; 7.65% 90 days.
                                                                                                       

   CERTIFICATES OF DEPOSIT: 7.48% one month; 7.53% two
months; 7.51% three months; 7.49% six months; 7.60% one year.
Average of top rates paid by major New York banks on primary
new issues of negotiable C.D.s, usually on amounts of $1
million and more. The minimum unit is $100,000. Typical rates
in the secondary market: 8.05% one month; 7.65% three months;
7.50% six months.
                                                                                                       

   BANKERS ACCEPTANCES: 8.45% 30 days; 7.80% 60 days; 7.63%
90 days; 7.50% 120 days; 7.37% 150 days; 7.22% 180 days.
Negotiable, bank-backed business credit instruments typically
financing an import order.
                                                                                                       

   LONDON LATE EURODOLLARS: 8 1/4% - 8 1/8% one month; 8
1/16% - 7 15/16% two months; 7 15/16% - 7 13/16% three
months; 7 7/8% - 7 3/4% four months; 7 3/4% - 7 5/8% five
months; 7 3/4% - 7 5/8% six months.
                                                                                                       

   LONDON INTERBANK OFFERED RATES (LIBOR): 8 1/4% one month;
7 15/16% three months; 7 11/16% six months; 7 5/8% one year.
The average of interbank offered rates for dollar deposits in
the London market based on quotations at five major banks.
Effective rate for contracts entered into two days from date
appearing at top of this column.
                                                                                                       

   FOREIGN PRIME RATES: Canada 12.75%; Germany 10.50%; Japan
8%; Switzerland 10.13%; Britain 14%. These rate indications
aren't directly comparable; lending practices vary widely by
location.
                                                                                                       

   TREASURY BILLS: Results of the Monday, December 17, 1990,
auction of short-term U.S. government bills, sold at a
discount from face value in units of $10,000 to $1 million:
6.78% 13 weeks; 6.77% 26 weeks.
                                                                                                       

   FEDERAL HOME LOAN MORTGAGE CORP. (Freddie Mac): Posted
yields on 30-year mortgage commitments for delivery within 30
days. 9.64%, standard conventional fixed-rate mortgages;
7.75%, 2% rate capped one-year adjustable rate mortgages.
Source: Telerate Systems Inc.
                                                                                                       

   FEDERAL NATIONAL MORTGAGE ASSOCIATION (Fannie Mae): Posted
yields on 30-year mortgage commitments for delivery within 30
days (priced at par). 9.56%, standard conventional fixed-rate
mortgages; 7.70%, 6/2 rate capped one-year adjustable rate
mortgages. Source: Telerate Systems Inc.
                                                                                                       

   MERRILL LYNCH READY ASSETS TRUST: 7.37%. Annualized
